    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Last Christmas when I made these, I made half of them with chocolate rather than jam (and the other half with  jam, but I think I used raspberry last year), and they were good that way.  I love chocolate as much as anyone, but I thought these particular cookies tasted better with jam than chocolate, because the jam provides that little kick of acid to counterbalance the richness of the browned butter, whereas chocolate blended in with them more, rather than standing out and providing a counterpoint.  If you see what I mean.  But the chocolate ones were quite good&#8211;I just found the jam ones better.</></>Congrats on the book.  I cannot wait&#8230;I&#8217;m hoping its publication will enable me to rid myself of the tangle of loose recipes I&#8217;ve printed off this site.  Ah, to have them all in one place&#8230;</p>
